1
00:00:39,679 --> 00:00:41,280
Old Chen, you've got sharp eyes.

2
00:00:41,399 --> 00:00:42,079
Bi Huaqiang.

3
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:43,840
Don't move.

4
00:00:47,119 --> 00:00:47,719
Uncle Min, didn't we

5
00:00:47,719 --> 00:00:48,840
have an agreement?

6
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:52,520
I wasn't finished talking, you know.

7
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,479
We can't damage the relics.

8
00:00:54,479 --> 00:00:56,320
If there really are Jueda ruins below,

9
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:57,439
one swing of your ice pick...

10
00:00:57,439 --> 00:00:58,719
Forget about how loud it'd be,

11
00:00:58,719 --> 00:00:59,960
or if it'd trigger an avalanche.

12
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,159
It's on you if ice smashes the relics.

13
00:01:03,759 --> 00:01:04,760
Then what do you suggest?

14
00:01:11,799 --> 00:01:13,480
This is an ice-melting agent.

15
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,560
Ginger juice.

16
00:01:14,879 --> 00:01:15,719
This stuff

17
00:01:15,799 --> 00:01:17,439
can melt through any thickness of ice.

18
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,719
Don't rush, just wait a moment.

19
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,760
That should be about right.

20
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,519
It's open.

21
00:01:40,599 --> 00:01:41,159
Xiao Qi.

22
00:01:41,879 --> 00:01:43,040
You stay up here.

23
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:43,519
Okay.

24
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:44,120
Old Lu.

25
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,400
You take care of An Xiang.

26
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:46,680
Fatty.

27
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,439
Don't worry, I've got Officer He.

28
00:01:50,799 --> 00:01:51,480
Get lost.

29
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,400
Come down with me.

30
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:13,879
Look.

31
00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:16,759
So many stone statues here.

32
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:18,800
But these statues

33
00:02:20,159 --> 00:02:21,919
all seem to face the same direction.

34
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,439
Fatty.

35
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:37,240
There's actually something here.

36
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,599
Looks like a pagoda.

37
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,719
Beautiful.

38
00:02:51,479 --> 00:02:52,280
What is it?

39
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,800
Let me see.

40
00:02:57,759 --> 00:02:58,960
There are paintings inside.

41
00:02:59,199 --> 00:03:00,159
Come over and take a look.

42
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,919
In these paintings,

43
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,639
the pagoda has nine tiers.

44
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:09,719
Not three.

45
00:03:10,479 --> 00:03:12,520
Three inner and three outer layers, right?

46
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,599
Add them up, doesn't that make nine?

47
00:03:13,599 --> 00:03:14,360
I get it now.

48
00:03:14,479 --> 00:03:15,280
What?

49
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,120
If that pagoda

50
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,800
symbolizes the Nine-Tiered Pagoda,

51
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:26,319
then the direction these statues face

52
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,120
should be where the Nine-Tiered Pagoda is.

53
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,800
Which way is it?

54
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,319
What's wrong?

55
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,000
What's going on?

56
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,599
What happened?

57
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:43,360
There seems to be something below.

58
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:44,599
Where?

59
00:03:45,479 --> 00:03:47,000
It looks like a snake.

60
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,360
A snake?

61
00:04:13,639 --> 00:04:15,000
Auntie He, Auntie He!

62
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,120
Auntie He!

63
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:28,079
This is the legendary

64
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,120
fire that can burn souls

65
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,720
to ashes,

66
00:04:37,839 --> 00:04:42,399
the Boundless Karmic Flame.

67
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:45,040
Auntie He!

68
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,519
Auntie He!

69
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,519
Ling La, Auntie He!

70
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:52,600
Ling La!

71
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,439
Ling La!

72
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:54,240
What's wrong with you?

73
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,360
If you keep shouting like this,

74
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:56,319
and it triggers an avalanche,

75
00:04:56,319 --> 00:04:57,319
we'll all be buried with her.

76
00:04:57,319 --> 00:04:57,920
Shut up!

77
00:04:59,079 --> 00:05:01,040
I say we really can't go any further.

78
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,639
Forget about the avalanche.

79
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,759
A life is at stake.

80
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:04,839
We have to head back now.

81
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:05,920
Take her back for emergency care.

82
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,639
That's right.

83
00:05:06,839 --> 00:05:08,480
Mission aborted. We're heading back.

84
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:08,959
Wait.

85
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:09,319
Let's go, let's go.

86
00:05:09,319 --> 00:05:10,199
Godfather.

87
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:12,839
Godfather!

88
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,879
Bi Huaqiang, move aside.

89
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:23,959
What about Godfather?

90
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,240
It's okay, it's okay.

91
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,959
We're home now.

92
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,439
I'm right here.

93
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,600
The pain will stop soon.

94
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,360
The pain will stop soon.

95
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:55,160
Now it won't hurt anymore.

96
00:05:56,759 --> 00:05:58,800
You won't suffer anymore.

97
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:14,360
Wait...

98
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,920
Are you out of your mind?

99
00:06:16,439 --> 00:06:17,720
She's your wife!

100
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,079
How could you do this to her?

101
00:06:22,199 --> 00:06:23,000
You... you... you...

102
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,240
You actually killed her!

103
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,040
Brother Chen.

104
00:06:32,439 --> 00:06:33,240
Ling La...

105
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:37,160
There was no way to save her anyway.

106
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:39,519
If I hadn't done this,

107
00:06:40,759 --> 00:06:42,079
everything we've worked for

108
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,160
would have been for nothing.

109
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,720
If she'd kept screaming like that,

110
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,920
all of us would've died here.

111
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,800
What I did

112
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,279
was for everyone's sake.

113
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:55,879
Ling La...

114
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,600
died pursuing the faith of civilization.

115
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,040
Her death was worth it.

116
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,800
I think this bastard's lost it.

117
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,439
He's a damn murderer!

118
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:11,839
The terrain here is dangerous.

119
00:07:12,639 --> 00:07:14,040
Let's talk once we reach safety.

120
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,439
Brother Chen.

121
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,240
Miss He is right.

122
00:07:21,079 --> 00:07:22,639
The mission cannot be canceled.

123
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,199
Who would've thought, beneath this ice,

124
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:45,279
there'd be such a vicious trap.

125
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:47,879
Under the ice must be a sealed chamber.

126
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,639
It holds a large amount of secret potion.

127
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:52,360
Years of being completely sealed off

128
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:55,160
let the potion fuse with the trapped air,

129
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,959
forming a special kind of gas.

130
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:58,480
The moment the ice breaks open,

131
00:07:58,519 --> 00:07:59,879
it ignites and burns.

132
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,240
So what happened?

133
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:09,560
They went and buried He Ling La.

134
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,680
That old guy's quite the actor.

135
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:14,120
The way he cried,

136
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:16,639
you'd think he wasn't the one who killed her.

137
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,680
That's a human life, you know!

138
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,079
Let me tell you,

139
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,680
these people are bad news.

140
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,839
If we keep going with them,

141
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:29,240
who knows what'll happen.

142
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,720
We can't travel with them anymore.

143
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,080
What do you guys think?

144
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:36,440
It's more than just not going with them.

145
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:38,279
This is a matter of right and wrong.

146
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,840
He killed someone.

147
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,159
We've got to report it to the police.

148
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,159
Yes, yes, yes.

149
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,360
Call the police! Call the police!

150
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:46,399
Here's what we do, let...

151
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,080
Let Brother Xiao Qi keep an eye on them.

152
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,200
We four will go report it in the county.

153
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:51,919
No way.

154
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,759
We can't leave Xiao Qi here alone.

155
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:56,200
They probably aren't fast asleep yet.

156
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,080
Let's wait a bit.

157
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:00,960
At 4 AM, we'll quietly make our move.

158
00:09:01,159 --> 00:09:03,080
We grab Xiao Qi and then go report it.

159
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,919
Good, good, good.

160
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,399
Commander Chen, what do you think?

161
00:09:09,639 --> 00:09:10,720
I'll go with the Chief of Staff.

162
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:11,919
All right.

163
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:13,639
I'll go find Xiao Qi now.

164
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:14,279
Okay.

165
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:20,759
Old Lu, Officer He.

166
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:22,440
You two pack up the gear.

167
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,000
So it'll be easy when we leave.

168
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:27,320
I... I'll catch some sleep. Wake me then.

169
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:30,759
Fatty.

170
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,720
Four o'clock.

171
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:17,480
You loser!

172
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,759
Brother Lu, it's you.

173
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,600
Still up, huh?

174
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,559
Let me tell you something.

175
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,720
This world is a messy place.

176
00:11:04,279 --> 00:11:06,840
A lot of people are ruthless.

177
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,480
You're still naive.

178
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,840
You've got a bright future ahead.

179
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:13,360
You need to stay on the right path.

180
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,519
Hold on, Brother Lu.

181
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:14,960
The right...

182
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,879
If you've got something to say, just say it.

183
00:11:16,879 --> 00:11:17,759
Go ahead, spit it out.

184
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,519
All right, I'll be blunt then.

185
00:11:21,279 --> 00:11:22,399
That godfather of yours...

186
00:11:22,639 --> 00:11:23,919
he's a nasty piece of work.

187
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,679
I'm telling you,

188
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,519
you'd better watch yourself.

189
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,120
What my godfather did to Auntie He,

190
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:33,039
he had no choice.

191
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:36,919
No choice, my foot.

192
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,840
Just look at that face of his.

193
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,679
Looks like a vicious demon.

194
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,279
Full of wicked schemes.

195
00:11:42,799 --> 00:11:44,879
If he dared to kill that He woman,

196
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:46,519
he'd kill you the next day.

197
00:11:47,559 --> 00:11:48,159
Look,

198
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,240
let me lay it out straight for you.

199
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,000
Anyway, we're...

200
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,440
making a run for it.

201
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,480
Tomorrow morning at four.

202
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,480
That's when we bolt.

203
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,919
If you wanna come with us,

204
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,440
be waiting right here at four.

205
00:12:01,799 --> 00:12:03,120
If you don't wanna come,

206
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,399
then forget it.

207
00:12:04,559 --> 00:12:05,440
Four o'clock.

208
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,279
Four.

209
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,360
Got it?

210
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,000
Let's go.

211
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,679
Move.

212
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,679
Commander Chen, please pick up the pace.

213
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:17,399
Go, go, go.

214
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,080
Hey, hey, don't push me!

215
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,000
So early?

216
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,399
Up this early, are you?

217
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,200
Brother Chen,

218
00:13:25,399 --> 00:13:27,120
fully armed in the dead of night,

219
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,320
where do you think you're going?

220
00:13:31,279 --> 00:13:33,600
Xiao Qi, what's this about?

221
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,279
I do what I'm paid for.

222
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:41,679
What's this little act you're putting on?

223
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:43,919
Honestly,

224
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,519
you and I should be in the same boat,

225
00:13:46,519 --> 00:13:47,919
sharing life and death.

226
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,039
Yet things have come to this.

227
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,440
All this gear here,

228
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,879
I paid for every bit of it.

229
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:54,799
You wanna leave? Fine.

230
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:56,320
Put down all my gear.

231
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,480
Then I won't stop you.

232
00:13:59,559 --> 00:14:00,360
You old fart.

233
00:14:01,039 --> 00:14:02,279
You're doing this on purpose, aren't you?

234
00:14:02,559 --> 00:14:04,240
Taking all our equipment away,

235
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,960
isn't that driving us to a dead end?

236
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:07,840
You're the ones who pushed me to this.

237
00:14:09,279 --> 00:14:09,879
You...

238
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,600
All right, all right, enough.

239
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,759
Fine.

240
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:22,919
I'll take you all along.

241
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:29,799
Brother Chen,

242
00:14:31,399 --> 00:14:33,559
you and I are tied to the same rope.

243
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:34,720
You can't get away,

244
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,200
and neither can I.

